# Server App Layout

All managed servers have a standardized `opt` Windows share accessible via UNC: `\\<server>\opt\`

On each server the share maps to a local drive (typically `E:\opt`), accessible as `$env:OptPath`.

## App Folders

Applications are organized by technology under `opt`:

| Folder | Technology | Example |
|--------|-----------|---------|
| `opt\FkPshApps\<AppName>\` | PowerShell | `opt\FkPshApps\Db2-ShadowDatabase\` |
| `opt\FkWinApps\<AppName>\` | Windows / .NET | `opt\FkWinApps\SomeService\` |
| `opt\FkPythonApps\<AppName>\` | Python | `opt\FkPythonApps\SomeScript\` |
| `opt\FkNodeApps\<AppName>\` | Node.js | `opt\FkNodeApps\SomeApi\` |

UNC pattern: `\\<server>\opt\Fk*Apps\<AppName>\<subfolders and files>`

## Data and Output Folders

Work files, exports, generated output, and app-specific logs live under:

```
opt\data\<AppName>\
```

Each app gets its own subfolder. Some apps create additional subfolders for run-specific output (e.g. `opt\data\Db2-ShadowDatabase\FKMVFTSH\20260304-060205\`).

## Shared Modules

PowerShell modules shared across all apps are deployed to:

```
opt\FkPshApps\CommonModules\
```

Deployed via `_Modules\_deploy.ps1` from the local dev machine.

## Central Config

Shared configuration files live on a central app server:

```
\\t-no1fkxtst-app\FkCommon\Configfiles\
```

Key file: `DatabasesV2.json` — the single source of truth for all DB2 servers, databases, instances, and applications.

## Deployment Pattern

Every app folder in the source repo may contain:

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `_deploy.ps1` | Deploys the app to target servers via `Deploy-Handler` |
| `_install.ps1` | One-time setup on the server (scheduled tasks, ACLs, etc.) |

Deploy copies files from the local dev machine to `\\<server>\opt\Fk*Apps\<AppName>\` via UNC.
